OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FFeeling seasonally warm, and in
OL,6,Fthe Central Belt very warm. Most dry
OL,7,Fwith sunny spells which turn hazy
OL,8,Fduring the afternoon as higher cloud
OL,9,Fincreases, but some patchy rain
OL,10,Fdevelop in Argyll, particularly from
OL,11,Fmid-afternoon. Southeast winds fresh
OL,12,Faround coasts.
OL,13,
OL,14,CTonight:FCloud thickening to bring
OL,15,Foccasional rain, this most persistent
OL,16,Facross Argyll where some heavier
OL,17,Foutbreaks may develop. Southerly
OL,18,Fcoastal winds initially fresh.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
